project GNUArgs

task ParseArgvWithSpecifiedValueOptions
    goal
        Parse argv given a set of option names that TAKE VALUES, so --name VAL and -n VAL work.
    input
        argv
        value_options
    output
        parsed
    constraint
        Function name is parse_gnu_args.
        Module is impl.py.
        Return value is a dict with keys flags, options, positional.
        --name=VAL is always an option regardless of value_options.
        --name (no =) consumes next token as value iff name is in value_options.
        -x consumes next token as value iff x is in value_options.
        Bare -- ends option parsing.
    test
        Empty argv returns empty buckets.
        Long flag without value: --verbose.
        Long option with equals: --count=3.
        Long option needing value: --count 3 when count is a value option.
        Short flag: -v.
        Short option needing value: -o out when o is a value option.
        Positional args pass through.
        Bare -- ends options.
        Missing value after value option raises ValueError.
        Non-list argv raises TypeError.
        Non-set value_options raises TypeError.
    success
        Every acceptance case above matches exactly.
